SIMPLE: aries
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aries
<hw>A"ri*es</hw>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The Ram; the first of the twelve
signs in the zodiac, which the sun enters at the vernal equinox, about
the 21st of March.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A constellation west of
Taurus, drawn on the celestial globe in the figure of a ram.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A battering-ram.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arietate</ent>⟦br⟧
